review_blob: Going on expectation from the label/deScription the beer is surprisingly disappointing.  Once you get over that, then you are left with a tasty malt led beer thats worth trying every year.

review_blob: The underlying Kernel IPA structure is there delivering the foundation for then hop characteristics to shine.  When those hops happen to be Citra, Cascade, Colombus & Centennial life is good.  Bottled on 07.Nov.12...

First salvo into the Christmas Beers.  Its great to be drinking this by an open fire.  Big, complex...all the right noises you would expect for an Imperial.  The 100 IBU listed on the bottle has me looking for the bitterness...something is there but not sure its hops.  Salut

Picked up a case from the brewery door, so my rating is after some consideration rather than a specific bottle.  Lying underneath is the recognisable Kernel IPA style.  Add the dryness from the rye & we are talking yummy

review_blob: My 2nd beer delving into French craft.  I like my Citras anyway but the effervescence & slight yeasty tang make this one that I will be trying again soon

Yummy. IPA with bite. This bad boy ride into your mouth and kick some series hop up your face. Drink up people. This is viking beer for the beer lover.

Yes this is wild beer and probably from a wild horse. Or maybe it has some horse hair added in at brew time. This would be a good one to drink right before you head into battle! Pillage time-o-rama. Dont let this put you off, Hornbeer do some amazing brews. Skol.

Seriously amazing pale ale. Classic style yet new and innovative. Using the Motueka hop from NZ:
 "New variety NZ Hop, this hop was bred by crossing a New Zealand breeding selection (2/3) with Saazer parentage (1/3). Primarily used for flavour and aroma its profile is citrus with lifted lemon and lime followed by a background of tropical fruit. Great in a Bohemian Pilsner." 

This hop adds pineapple+lemon with a dry cloud forest finish. The beer a ittle cloudy but that just adds character to a sweet brew. The BV Crew rarely give out 18/20. This one deserves it.

Wow this one really hits you in the right way. Like a hot girl you didnt notice getting onto the train (or bus). I mean the color, the taste and the finish is sweet. The finish lingers and has real apple+bop+malt bite.
beer_name: The Kernel Amber Ale Amarillo Kohatu

review_blob: amber colour, slight sweet carmel aroma. Not much head. Looks like a solid bottled bitter. taste a bit malty with a hint of hay or grassy in a good way.
We love this one in the nano keg (ie, cans), Has to be the best beer available in a can in Europe!
Very very nice. But not as good as the hype, but hey thats more down to personal taste. A seriously top rated SD style double IPA!

One words: Awesome! This is very drinkable beer. I would call a cross between a pale ale + amber + IPA. Only 5%. 18/20 puts this in the top end of the BV crew.
The mini keg is the way to go with the beer. Keep it cold and keep it coming.
